        "body": "<p>Skin on the Sunshine Coast is exposed to conditions rarely seen elsewhere in the world.</p><p><strong>Intense Ultraviolet Radiation</strong> — Queensland consistently records some of the highest UV indexes globally. Prolonged UV exposure breaks down collagen fibres and increases oxidative stress within the skin.</p><p><strong>Coastal Exposure</strong> — Salt air and wind can dehydrate the skin barrier while increasing transepidermal water loss.</p><p><strong>Heat and Humidity</strong> — Humidity can increase oil production while heat accelerates inflammation and barrier disruption.</p><p>These environmental conditions require a skincare approach that supports <strong>skin function and resilience</strong>, not simply cosmetic improvement.</p>",
